FIT Academic Senate 
The FIT Academic Senate is the highest autonomous representative body of FIT CTU.  Besides other powers granted by the Higher Education Act, the Academic Senate elects or dismisses the Dean, approves the faculty budget, approves internal regulations of the faculty including admission regulations, approves proposals for nominating or dismissing members of the Scientific Board, and approves the long-term strategic plan of the faculty.
The FIT Academic Senate has 10 members. Six members are elected from among the FIT academic staff, four members are elected from among FIT students.


 


